Boqun Electronics iConsole SDK User Manual
Welcome to the iConsole SDK User Manual! This manual provides detailed instructions to help you quickly learn how to use the iConsole SDK to develop fitness equipment electronic watch applications for the Android platform.
Special Recommendation

Starting from v2.0.0, iConsole SDK supports bicycles, treadmills, and rowing machines
Starting from v2.0.0, iConsole SDK has been refactored with a new API. For details, please refer to v2.0.0 API Document

Catalog

Update Log
Quick Use
Class reference

Demos and Example Projects

Bike

Treadmill

Rower

Example (GitHub): This project includes an introduction to the control functions of a bicycle, treadmill, and rowing machine.

UpdateLog.html.title: Update log
UpdateLog.html.body:
Update Log
This log starts in November 2021, no change logs were recorded before then.
 
v2.2.9->v2.2.10 Changelog 2025.01.17

New FTMS communication command for treadmills

v2.2.8->v2.2.9 Changelog 2024.11.13

New FTMS communication commands and VR correction commands for rowing machines

v2.2.7->v2.2.8 Changelog 2024.11.05

Added 8 custom external key communications for bicycles

v2.2.6->v2.2.7 Changelog 2024.05.11

Treadmill communication increases negative lift

v2.2.5->v2.2.6 Changelog 2024.05.11

When the treadmill, rowing machine, and bicycle communication fails to obtain the ClientID, the default value returned is changed from 0 to -1.

v2.1.2 —> v2.1.9 Changelog 2022.11.01
Deprecated APIs will be removed in future versions. Please switch to new APIs as soon as possible.

Add BoQunTreadmill.init(OnTreadmillListener listener) replace BoQunTreadmill.init() 和 BoQunTreadmill.setOnTreadmillListener(OnTreadmillListener)

Deprecation BoQunTreadmill.init()

Deprecation BoQunTreadmill.setOnTreadmillListener(OnTreadmillListener)

Add BoQunRower.init(OnRowerListener listener) replace BoQunRower.init()  and BoQunRower.setOnRowerListener(OnRowerListenerl)

Deprecation BoQunRower.init()

Deprecation BoQunRower.setOnRowerListener(OnRowerListenerl)

Added BoQunBike.init(OnBikeListener listener) replace BoQunBike.init() 和 BoQunBike.setBikeListener(OnBikeListener l)

Added BoQunBike.setSportData(time, speed, distance, calories, rpm, pulse, watt)

Added BoQunBike.setSportParams(code,value)

Deprecation BoQunBike.init()

Deprecation BoQunBike.setBikeListener(OnBikeListener l)


2022.3.25

Added BikeStatusCallback
Added  BikeStatusCallbacks
Added  BikeStatusCallbacks.FTMSStateCallback

2021.12.30

Added  TreadmillStatusCallback
Added  TreadmillStatusCallbacks
Added  TreadmillStatusCallbacks.SafetyKeyStatusCallback  replace onSafetyKeyStateChange
Added  TreadmillStatusCallbacks.CoolDownStatusCallback  replace onCoolDownStateChange
Added  TreadmillStatusCallbacks.UnmannedStateDetectionCallback
Modify OnTreadmillListener, delete onCoolDownStateChange, onSafetyKeyStateChange

2021.11.16

Added  BoQunRower

Added  BoQunRowerFactory


2021.11.14

Added  BoQunTreadmill

Added  BoQunTreadmillFactory


2021.11.10

Added  BoQunBike

Added  BoQunBikeFactory

BikeApi.html.title: Bike
BikeApi.html.body:
Bike API




BoQunBike



Parameter
Description




BoQunBike.TYPE_SPORT_STATUS
Sport status. Use queryMachineInfo to query and then call back onResponseSportStatus


BoQunBike.TYPE_LOAD_LEVEL
Resistance level, query using queryMachineInfo and then call back onResponseLoadLevel






Function
Description




BoQunBike.init(OnBikeListener listener)
Initializes the serial port and returns a Boolean value indicating whether the serial port was successfully initialized.


BoQunBike.queryConfigInfo()
Query the bicycle configuration information resistance, lifting range, status, etc., callback onResponseConfigInfo, read failure callback onError


BoQunBike.queryMachineInfo( int type)
Query bicycle information, parameter type


BoQunBike.start()
Start exercising, call back onResponseSportStatus after successful start, and start transmitting data onResponseSportData


BoQunBike.pause()
Pause the sport. After the sport is successfully paused, the onResponseSportStatus callback is called. During the pause state, the sport data will not be transmitted.


BoQunBike.stop()
Stop exercising, call back onResponseSportStatus


BoQunBike.setLoadLevel( int load )
Control the resistance level of the bicycle, callback onResponseLoadLevel, the larger the load value, the greater the resistance, the load has a range limit, the load range parameter reads BikeConfigInfo


BoQunBike.setInclineLevel( int incline )
Control the bicycle incline level, callback onResponseInclineLevel, the larger the incline value, the higher the incline. The incline has a range limit, and the incline range parameter reads BikeConfigInfo


BoQunBike.setFanLevel( int level)
Control the fan wind speed level, callback onResponseFanLevel, the wind speed level supports 0-3 levels, if the machine does not have a fan, it does not support adjustment, get whether the machine has a fan status BikeConfigInfo


BoQunBike.setWorkMode( int mode)
Set the bicycle lower computer working mode BikeWorkMode


BoQunBike.setFTMSEnabled( boolean enable)
Enable or disable FMTS. It must be used with a lower control board with FMTS function. Callback BikeStatusCallbacks.FTMSStateCallback


BoQunBike.setSerialPortEnabled( boolean enable)
Enable and disable the serial port. The default is enabled. This method is provided to facilitate handling special situations. For example, multiple apps reading the serial port at the same time will cause mutual interference. This method can be used to avoid tips: It will not really close the serial port, but it will definitely not read the serial port data


BoQunBike.setSportData(long time, float speed, float distance, int calories, int rpm, int pulse, int watt)
When the APP and the electronic watch display exercise data synchronously, it is usually necessary to send the exercise data to the lower computer. If there is no requirement, please ignore it- time unit: seconds, range (0-65535)- speed unit: kilometers per hour, range (0-65535)- distance unit: km, range (0-65535)- calories unit: kcal, range (0-65535)- rpm range (0-65535)- pulse range (0-65535)- watt range (0-65535)


BoQunBike.setSportParams(@BikeSportParams int code, int value)
Set sport parameters. Ignore if not requiredSee BikeSportParams for parameter details


BoQunBike.setBikeListener(OnBikeListener listener)
Bicycle Listener (deprecated)


BoQunBike.registerStateListener(BikeStatusCallback callback)
Register status callback listener


BoQunBike.unregisterStateListener(BikeStatusCallback callback)
Unregister status callback listener


BoQunBike.unregisterAllStateListener()
Unregister all status callback listeners


BoQunBike.destroy()
Destroy the instance and release resources







BikeWorkMode



Parameter
Description




BikeWorkMode.NORMAL
This state should be set when the TFT screen is on and enters the working state


BikeWorkMode.SLEEP
This state should be set when the TFT screen is off and enters sleep mode


BikeWorkMode.SHUT_DOWN
This state should be set when TFT is turned off to release resources







BikeStatusCallback



Function
Description




void onBikeSportStateChange(int status)
Bicycle status change callback







BikeStatusCallbacks
This class mainly implements status callback. It currently supports monitoring FTMS status. Other functions will be implemented later if needed, or you can inherit the BikeStatusCallback interface to implement custom status callback.
Currently implements FMTS switch status callback
BoQunBike.registerStateListener(new BikeStatusCallbacks.FTMSStateCallback() {
            @Override
            public void onFTMSStateChange(boolean enable) {
                 //Enable and disable status
            }
        });

Remember to unregister
BoQunBike.unregisterStateListener(xxxx);

//Or, look at your personal application scenarios and needs
BoQunBike.unregisterAllStateListener();





OnBikeListener



Function
Description




void onResponseConfigInfo(BikeConfigInfo info)
Reply to the control configuration information


void onResponseSportStatus(@BikeSportState int status)
Respond to sport status, parameter: status


void onResponseSportData(int stepCount, int rpm, int heartRate)
Reply to exercise datastepCount: number of steps (accumulated value)rpm: revolutions per minuteheartRate: heart rate when holding the hand


void onResponseLoadLevel(int load)
Restore the resistance level of the lower control


void onResponseInclineLevel(int incline)
Resume control and ascend level


void onResponseFanLevel(int level)
Reset fan speed level


void onExternalKeyEvent(@BikeKeyCode int keyCode)
Pressing an external key on the panel (some UP and DOWN buttons can be long pressed) triggers a callback and replies BikeKeyCode


void onError(int errorCode)
Error callback occurs, parameters see ErrorCode, treadmill down-control error code will also be called back, but the treadmill error code depends on the error code provided by the docking motor manufacturer.







BikeSportState



Parameter
Description




BikeSportState.STOP
Stop state


BikeSportState.START
Starting state


BikeSportState.PAUSE
Pause state

void onResponseInclineAutoCorrection(@AutoCorrectionStateint state, int inclineADC)
Respond to the auto-correction status and ADC value, parameter: state







AutoCorrectionState
inclineADC: value range 0-255. ADC will keep changing during the calibration of the lifting motor. Normally, it will change from small to large, and from large to small is a complete calibration.

For example, multiple APPs reading the serial port at the same time will cause mutual interference. TreadmillStatusCallback
This is an interface class, treadmill state change and motion state change callback



Function
Description




void onTreadmillSportStateChange(int state);
Motion state change callback


void onTreadmillStateChange(int state,int speed);
Treadmill status changes







TreadmillStatusCallbacks
​       This class mainly implements some abstract class monitoring status callbacks. Currently, it supports security key status monitoring, CoolDown mode, FTMS status monitoring, and unmanned motion monitoring. Other functions will be implemented later if needed, or you can inherit the TreadmillStatusCallback interface to implement custom status callbacks.
Currently, FMTS switch status callbacks are implemented
//Security KEY status monitoring
BoQunTreadmill.registerStateListener(new TreadmillStatusCallbacks.SafetyKeyStatusCallback() {
       @Override
       public void onSafetyKeyStatus(boolean normal) {
            //normal==true //Security Key Insertion
            //normal==false //Safety Key removal
       }
});
//CoolDown Mode Monitoring
BoQunTreadmill.registerStateListener(new TreadmillStatusCallbacks.CoolDownStatusCallback() {
       /**
        * status:

        * CoolDownState.START    COOL DOWN mode starts to slow down
        * CoolDownState.ING      During deceleration, the speed value will become smaller and smaller
        * CoolDownState.END      Cool down mode ends
        *
        * speed:Real-time speed
        */
       @Override
       public void onCoolDownStatus(int status, int speed) {

       }
});

//Unmanned motion monitoring
long detectionTime=45;//Detection time of no movement, unit: second

BoQunTreadmill.registerStateListener(
    new TreadmillStatusCallbacks.UnmannedStateDetectionCallback(detectionTime) {
       @Override
       public void onUnmannedStateDetection(boolean isUnmanned, long time) {
           //isUnmanned Whether there is no movement at present. When the time of no movement exceeds the detection time, it will become true.
           //time Start counting the time when no one is exercising
       }
});

//FTMS Enable status monitoring
BoQunTreadmill.registerStateListener(new TreadmillStatusCallbacks.FTMSStateCallback() {
            @Override
            public void onFTMSStateChange(boolean enable) {
                Log.d(TAG, "onFTMSStateChange: " + enable);
            }
        });
        BoQunTreadmill.setFTMSEnabled(true);

Remember to unregister
BoQunTreadmill.unregisterStateListener(xxxx);

//Or, look at your personal application scenarios and needs
BoQunTreadmill.unregisterAllStateListener();
